        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=68692&amp;TOPIC_ID=8106&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Anyone+eles+get+this+yet%3F%2E%3F%2E%3F%2E%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         you guys apparently misunderstood the point i was trying to convey.. so i'll use an example instead.</P><P>a group of 6 (chanter, necro, wizard, warrior, monk, and cleric) are killing stuff in zone XYZ. Warrior decides hes bored waiting for the monk to pull and decides to taunt Pet_01 while he waits (he gains aggro on the pet, but the pet cant attack him at this point) meanwhile the monk has INC. just as INC mobs arrive at the group the owner of Pet_01 goes LD, suddenly the pet is no longer flagged as a pet and can now attack PCs... it still has aggro from the warrior taunting and launches its attack...</P><P>like i said, there used to be a way to do this on purpose using certain spells.. but i think they fixed that awhile ago... it was pretty funny to make your pet a pissed off NPC and then FD and watch him go ape on the players around you.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
